Wash and dry produce.

Halve, deseed, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1}(halved, deseeded and thinly sliced crosswise) into strips. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced, whites separated from greens).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{}, over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%oz}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Ground turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add green pepper and cook, stirring, until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. TIP: If needed, add a splash of water to help green pepper soften.

Add green pepper to pan with beef or turkey (skip the oil); cook through this step as instructed.

While green pepper cooks, drain and rinse @black beans{1%can}.

Once green pepper is softened, stir in scallion whites and @Southwest spice blend{2%tsp} (4 tsp for 4 servings; be sure to measure—we sent more). Cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add beans, @Tex-Mex paste{1%unit}, and @water{1/4%cup}. Cook, stirring, until filling has combined and thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Sprinkle bean filling with @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup} and @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}. Cover pan until cheese melts, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with bean filling, @smoky red pepper crema{2%tbsp}, and scallion greens. Serve.